node.text: Before we wrap up one of the wildest years, we’re taking a look back at our favorite @stockxteam highlights. Through it all, the crew shattered records, launched campaigns, supported important causes, partnered with insanely talented collaborators, AND hit $2.8 billy - all thanks to YOU. 2021, we’re ready for ya 😤

node.text: Two specially-crafted decks and t-shirts from @berrics and @everybodyskates are now available exclusively on StockX. Designed by legendary pro @alphonzorawls, this limited ‘Thank You’ collection pays homage to the diversity within skateboarding, featuring the names of influential Black and Brown skateboarders from the last 40 years. Limited quantities are up for grabs, so tap fast to secure yours. A portion of proceeds will support the @nextupfound.

node.text: Jordan Brand strikes twice with the highly-anticipated AJ4 Retro Lightning release. The OG colorway first debuted in 2006, and now 15 years later, it’s back and true to form. A vibrant Tour Yellow takes center stage across the upper and tongue, while black netted panels, dark grey accents, and a white midsole add a balanced contrast. Miss the drop? Tap to shop.

node.text:
The perfect pair for late summer rounds. Tap fast to secure an early release of the brand new @malbongolf x @newbalance 997G, exclusively via DropX. 

Inspired by the iconic caddie uniforms of The Masters, these shoes come correct in a crisp all white colorway with a pop of green trim. The gum sole gives a nice nod to OG sneaker culture, and the Cush+ insole offers premium comfort for playing any course. Plus, each pair includes a limited golf towel featuring StockX and Malbon Golf co-branding. 

Only 250 pairs are up for grabs. Link in bio for more.

node.text: Virgil Abloh is set to deliver 50 pairs of his latest Off-White x Dunk Low collab, each donning a uniquely colored tongue, liner, laces, zip tie, lot number, and Swoosh. The massive “Dear Summer” pack, also dubbed “The 50”, features 48 iterations of a white and gray design, while the first lot comes laced in all white, and the final lot is dressed in all black. Tap to shop.

node.text: For her fifth Jordan Brand collab, designer Aleali May returns with a refined take on the Air Jordan 14. Inspired by jade and gold jewelry from her grandmothers, May incorporates premium elements like a vibrant marbled green midsole and a metallic shank plate. A neutral suede upper rounds out the elevated look. Tap to shop the women’s exclusive early.
